# 3. Live Testnet Rollout Plan
This is where most projects collapse. Timing + sequencing matters.
Phase 0 — Dry Run (Internal)
Local fork simulation
Full commit → reveal → settlement cycle
Validate entropy + ordering
Phase 1 — Closed Testnet
Deploy on Sepolia
Invite limited wallets
Stress test:
commit spam
invalid reveals
edge timing
Phase 2 — Public Testnet (State Activation)
Run it like a ritual, not a launch.
Timeline
Day 1 — State 1–3
Contracts deployed
Genesis hash published
Day 2 — State 4
Commit window opens
Day 3 — State 5
Commit window closes
Day 4 — State 6
Reveal phase
Day 5 — State 7–8
Entropy injected
Allocation computed
Settlement executed
Day 6 — State 9–12
Liquidity simulated
Final state hash published
Metrics to Track
Participation rate
Reveal completion %
Gas fairness (variance)
Allocation distribution curve
Failure Conditions
Low reveal rate → UX issue
Entropy predictability → redesign
Gas spikes → batching failure
